<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1768] unions can&apos;t have required fields (Compiler)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1768</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Required fields within unions should issue a warning. First, required makes not much sense with unions. Next, most languages are already treating them as optional anyway, effectively ignoring the required attribute.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12618239">THRIFT-1768</key>
            <summary>unions can&apos;t have required fields (Compiler)</summary>
